00:32:53,375 --> 00:32:54,375
NAIROBI: What's up?

490
00:32:54,458 --> 00:32:56,250
You gonna hug me or what?

491
00:33:04,166 --> 00:33:06,791
- Cheers to the baby.
- Be quiet or the baby will wake up.

492
00:33:06,875 --> 00:33:08,583
Say it with an Argentinian accent.

493
00:33:08,666 --> 00:33:11,833
(IN ARGENTINEAN ACCENT)
<i>Che, boludo. </i>Congratulations.

494
00:33:11,916 --> 00:33:13,125
(LAUGHS)

495
00:33:13,208 --> 00:33:16,041
That is the worst Argentinian accent
I've heard in my life.

496
00:33:16,125 --> 00:33:18,833
- Your house is beautiful.
- DENVER: It feels like heaven here.

497
00:33:18,916 --> 00:33:21,000
- And Rio?
- DENVER: He knows it.

498
00:33:21,083 --> 00:33:21,958
Rio isn't coming.

499
00:33:25,833 --> 00:33:26,958
He was arrested.

500
00:33:28,791 --> 00:33:29,750
When?

501
00:33:30,458 --> 00:33:32,583
17 days ago on an island in the Caribbean.

502
00:33:34,083 --> 00:33:36,083
It hasn't been made public yet.

503
00:33:36,833 --> 00:33:38,375
He's in some shit hole being tortured.

504
00:33:39,875 --> 00:33:41,083
How did they find him?

505
00:33:44,208 --> 00:33:45,625
He was using a satellite phone.

506
00:33:51,333 --> 00:33:52,541
Was he in trouble?

507
00:33:53,041 --> 00:33:54,333
No.

508
00:33:58,916 --> 00:34:00,666
(SIGHS) There were rules.

509
00:34:02,375 --> 00:34:03,291
No Europe.

510
00:34:03,375 --> 00:34:05,041
No access to phones.

511
00:34:05,125 --> 00:34:06,875
What the fuck are we doing here?

512
00:34:07,875 --> 00:34:09,166
You're here for safety reasons.

513
00:34:09,750 --> 00:34:12,750
What safety reasons?
Rio didn't know where we were.

514
00:34:12,833 --> 00:34:13,750
TOKYO: Guys…

515
00:34:15,416 --> 00:34:16,375
we have to help him.

516
00:34:16,458 --> 00:34:20,291
Come on, come on, come on.
What the fuck are we doing here?

517
00:34:21,291 --> 00:34:23,791
Are you actually thinking
we're gonna rescue Rio?

518
00:34:23,875 --> 00:34:24,833
Yes, Denver.

519
00:34:27,583 --> 00:34:29,041
That's what I'm thinking.

520
00:34:31,750 --> 00:34:33,125
(BANGS TABLE)

521
00:34:33,208 --> 00:34:35,666
(SIGHS)

522
00:34:36,750 --> 00:34:38,291
Mother fucker.

523
00:34:40,583 --> 00:34:43,500
You made me cross the world
with a small baby to tell me this shit?

524
00:34:43,583 --> 00:34:46,333
- Are you smoking opium, Professor?
- Denver, sit down.

525
00:34:46,416 --> 00:34:48,208
What do you think this is? A video game?

526
00:34:48,291 --> 00:34:50,208
- You're not my fucking boss!
- Sit down.

527
00:34:50,791 --> 00:34:52,500
You owe me this fucking life!

528
00:34:53,083 --> 00:34:54,291
Do you understand that?!

529
00:34:54,375 --> 00:34:56,916
You owe me all of this.
That fucking backyard.

530
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:00,375
Even that fucking sea
because you can't bring my father back.

531
00:35:00,458 --> 00:35:01,458
Do you get that?

532
00:35:03,833 --> 00:35:04,875
I have a son.

533
00:35:05,583 --> 00:35:09,666
I fucking swear I'm not gonna let him
suffer as much as I did.

534
00:35:09,750 --> 00:35:10,916
Go and ask him

535
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:13,583
if he wants his father's body
to be full of bullets.

536
00:35:13,666 --> 00:35:15,125
- Ask him.
- Denver.

537
00:35:16,833 --> 00:35:19,750
They have him in a bathtub
with a bag over his head.

538
00:35:19,833 --> 00:35:22,666
- Do you understand?
- I am sorry but that's his problem.

539
00:35:22,750 --> 00:35:23,875
PROFESSOR: That face

540
00:35:24,708 --> 00:35:26,083
you're looking at right now

541
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:30,750
is the same face your dad was looking at
while you were trying to open the tunnel.

542
00:35:34,458 --> 00:35:36,416
She didn't leave his side for a second.

543
00:35:38,750 --> 00:35:40,083
Tokyo was there.

544
00:35:44,750 --> 00:35:46,041
Rio made a mistake.

545
00:35:49,583 --> 00:35:51,000
You also made mistakes.

546
00:35:52,375 --> 00:35:55,666
You took your father up to the roof.
You two could've been killed.

547
00:35:56,375 --> 00:35:57,791
But the gang was there.

548
00:36:00,208 --> 00:36:03,458
Helsinki, you took the car
to the scrapyard, but didn't crush it.

549
00:36:03,958 --> 00:36:05,125
We fixed it.

550
00:36:05,625 --> 00:36:07,083
The gang was there.

551
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:10,291
You were late to stop the machines,

552
00:36:11,666 --> 00:36:12,833
Nairobi.

553
00:36:13,958 --> 00:36:15,250
And the police came in.

554
00:36:17,333 --> 00:36:19,875
You escaped through the tunnel
because Berlin…

555
00:36:21,708 --> 00:36:24,375
stayed there to hold them back.

556
00:36:24,875 --> 00:36:27,250
He gave us the seconds we needed.

557
00:36:27,958 --> 00:36:29,083
The gang was there.

558
00:36:31,791 --> 00:36:33,000
The one who isn't here…

559
00:36:37,666 --> 00:36:38,500
is Berlin…

560
00:36:40,541 --> 00:36:41,541
and Oslo…

561
00:36:44,666 --> 00:36:45,625
and Moscow.

562
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,416
What the fuck?

563
00:37:03,416 --> 00:37:04,416
She's one of us.

564
00:37:09,125 --> 00:37:10,416
I made a mistake.

565
00:37:12,125 --> 00:37:13,083
I lost control.

566
00:37:14,541 --> 00:37:15,833
The gang was there.

567
00:37:28,708 --> 00:37:30,250
Now Rio's made a mistake

568
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,208
like the rest of us.

569
00:37:35,083 --> 00:37:37,208
I can't ask you to feel what I feel, but…

570
00:37:40,375 --> 00:37:42,333
But I really feel responsible

571
00:37:43,791 --> 00:37:44,625
that some

572
00:37:45,500 --> 00:37:46,708
son of a bitch

573
00:37:48,875 --> 00:37:51,916
is giving him electric shocks
as he hangs from his ankles.

574
00:37:55,625 --> 00:37:57,041
(SIGHS)

575
00:38:00,208 --> 00:38:01,041
I'm going!

576
00:38:05,208 --> 00:38:06,375
Not alone, Nairobi.

577
00:38:07,875 --> 00:38:10,791
Because if you're going, I'm going too.

578
00:38:12,083 --> 00:38:13,458
Here we fucking go.

579
00:38:29,500 --> 00:38:31,500
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYS)

580
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,583
TOKYO: How will we rescue Rio?

581
00:38:54,208 --> 00:38:56,875
PROFESSOR: With a robbery.
That's what we're good at.

582
00:38:57,458 --> 00:38:59,041
TOKYO: Rescue him with a robbery?

583
00:38:59,541 --> 00:39:00,791
PROFESSOR: We will begin

584
00:39:01,375 --> 00:39:02,250
with a robbery.

585
00:39:03,416 --> 00:39:04,250
TOKYO: But…

586
00:39:06,458 --> 00:39:08,833
But actually we're gonna
defy the establishment.

587
00:39:11,833 --> 00:39:15,583
This time, we won't be those guys
who take hostages to make their own money.

588
00:39:17,666 --> 00:39:19,416
We'll be the ones who take a stand.

589
00:39:22,125 --> 00:39:24,375
The ones who say, "Enough is enough."

590
00:39:25,291 --> 00:39:28,125
What they're doing to Rio
is a declaration of war.

591
00:39:29,041 --> 00:39:30,708
And we're the resistance.

592
00:39:31,916 --> 00:39:32,750
No?

593
00:39:34,708 --> 00:39:36,208
TOKYO: What are we gonna rob?

594
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:38,875
The gold.

595
00:39:38,958 --> 00:39:39,791
Gold?

596
00:39:41,291 --> 00:39:42,125
Not just gold.

597
00:39:43,333 --> 00:39:44,208
<i>The</i> gold.

598
00:39:45,166 --> 00:39:46,541
The only gold that matters.

599
00:39:50,125 --> 00:39:52,250
The National Reserve at the Bank of Spain.

600
00:39:55,083 --> 00:39:56,625
Isn't that gonna be a big mess?

601
00:39:56,708 --> 00:39:58,291
Never been a bigger one.

602
00:39:59,416 --> 00:40:02,083
You just thought of this now,
while watching the sunrise?

603
00:40:07,125 --> 00:40:08,666
PROFESSOR: No, it's not my plan.

604
00:40:09,166 --> 00:40:10,458
TOKYO: Your father's?

605
00:40:10,541 --> 00:40:12,541
("BELLA CIAO" PLAYS)

606
00:40:14,583 --> 00:40:16,208
PROFESSOR: No, not my father's.

607
00:40:22,208 --> 00:40:25,208
{\an8}FLORENCE, FIVE YEARS UNTIL D-DAY

608
00:40:27,625 --> 00:40:29,291
(CHURCH BELLS RING)

609
00:40:41,166 --> 00:40:42,375
PROFESSOR: Andrés.

610
00:40:42,458 --> 00:40:45,125
(UPBEAT ITALIAN MUSIC PLAYS)

611
00:40:46,375 --> 00:40:49,333
(LAUGHS) Little brother.

612
00:40:52,916 --> 00:40:54,208
(CHUCKLES)

613
00:40:58,083 --> 00:40:59,666
(IN ITALIAN) Welcome to Italy.

614
00:41:00,708 --> 00:41:03,416
(IN ENGLISH) A country
full of art and class…

615
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:05,583
where everyone dresses with style.

616
00:41:06,208 --> 00:41:07,375
Unlike you.

617
00:41:07,458 --> 00:41:09,166
You look like a salesman.

618
00:41:13,875 --> 00:41:15,958
Come with me. (CHUCKLES)

619
00:41:21,541 --> 00:41:22,958
Off to my humble abode.

620
00:41:23,875 --> 00:41:25,833
I have so many things I wanna tell you.

621
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:38,375
This is your home?
"The abode in the country"?

622
00:41:39,500 --> 00:41:42,833
You begin by looking for something
with two bathrooms and a garden,

623
00:41:42,916 --> 00:41:45,125
and you end up renovating a monastery.

624
00:41:50,083 --> 00:41:53,333
- I know how to break into the Royal Mint.
- Through the front door?

625
00:41:53,416 --> 00:41:55,750
The back.
On the truck with the currency paper.

626
00:41:59,791 --> 00:42:01,208
Andrés, there's people here.

627
00:42:01,291 --> 00:42:04,375
Relax, we don't bother each other.
They're the perfect neighbors.

628
00:42:04,458 --> 00:42:06,166
- PROFESSOR: They're monks.
- Cistercians.

629
00:42:06,250 --> 00:42:08,458
They live on one wing
and we're on the other.

630
00:42:08,541 --> 00:42:10,750
Besides, they're sworn to silence.

631
00:42:10,833 --> 00:42:14,625
They've taken a vow of silence,
not at gunpoint or before a judge,

632
00:42:14,708 --> 00:42:16,291
but before God Almighty.

633
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,125
Makes things much more interesting, right?

634
00:42:21,666 --> 00:42:22,541
PROFESSOR: And…

635
00:42:22,625 --> 00:42:24,333
um… what did you tell them?

636
00:42:24,416 --> 00:42:27,250
BERLIN: That I'm an intellectual
in need of austerity and solitude,

637
00:42:27,333 --> 00:42:30,000
so I can write a treatise
on theological philosophy.

638
00:42:30,083 --> 00:42:31,250
And they believed you?

639
00:42:31,333 --> 00:42:32,916
I also paid for the renovations

640
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:36,125
so they didn't have to turn
this beautiful place into a hotel.

641
00:42:36,208 --> 00:42:38,375
They don't need much. They love me.

642
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:41,666
Sometimes I sing
Gregorian chants with them.

643
00:42:42,166 --> 00:42:44,125
- (DOOR OPENS)
- BERLIN: Watch your head.

644
00:42:46,708 --> 00:42:48,583
Andrés, do you sleep in a cell?

645
00:42:48,666 --> 00:42:51,750
Well, I intended to, but I fell in love…

646
00:42:53,958 --> 00:42:54,875
with this chapel.

647
00:42:55,375 --> 00:42:56,916
(CHUCKLES)

648
00:42:58,875 --> 00:42:59,791
(LAUGHS)

649
00:43:00,375 --> 00:43:01,375
Look at this beauty.

650
00:43:02,791 --> 00:43:05,250
(CELESTIAL MUSIC PLAYS)

651
00:43:28,583 --> 00:43:32,291
Sergio, my dear friend. How are you?
Long time no see. Come here.

652
00:43:32,375 --> 00:43:33,291
What is this?

653
00:43:34,208 --> 00:43:37,541
Do you remember that old plan
to steal gold from the Bank of Spain?

654
00:43:37,625 --> 00:43:41,833
It's remarkable. We can obtain up to
90 tons of gold from the inside there.

655
00:43:42,333 --> 00:43:45,875
We found a way to do it
and I think you're gonna love it.

656
00:43:45,958 --> 00:43:49,583
It's the most brilliant civil engineering
since the Panama Canal. I guarantee it.

657
00:43:49,666 --> 00:43:52,708
No. Wait a minute. Wait.
I've told you a million times.

658
00:43:52,791 --> 00:43:54,458
You can get the gold, but, Andrés,

659
00:43:54,541 --> 00:43:56,875
there's no way you'll leave
the Bank of Spain alive.

660
00:43:58,083 --> 00:44:01,500
Well, that's just a small detail.
The gold comes first.

661
00:44:01,583 --> 00:44:03,916
- Then the people, right Andrés?
- That's right.

662
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:07,041
- What do you mean "small detail"?
- Let's think about all that later.

663
00:44:07,125 --> 00:44:09,583
Brother, do you notice
something different about me?

664
00:44:09,666 --> 00:44:12,208
- No.
- I have to tell you about a woman. Come.

665
00:44:14,791 --> 00:44:15,791
Take a look.

666
00:44:16,583 --> 00:44:17,583
My sweetheart.

667
00:44:18,583 --> 00:44:20,083
May I present Tatiana.

668
00:44:21,208 --> 00:44:22,458
She's very beautiful.

669
00:44:22,541 --> 00:44:24,125
She's madly in love with me.

670
00:44:24,750 --> 00:44:26,583
- (CHUCKLES)
- She's a goddess.

671
00:44:27,500 --> 00:44:29,250
BERLIN: I think he's gonna like her.

672
00:44:31,208 --> 00:44:32,875
TOKYO: <i>What the Professor never imagined</i>

673
00:44:34,250 --> 00:44:35,416
<i>was that one day</i>

674
00:44:36,125 --> 00:44:39,041
<i>he would have to make</i>
<i>that suicidal plan his own.</i>

675
