<i>♪ That's all I want ♪</i>

680
00:45:20,208 --> 00:45:24,875
<i>♪ I don't care at all ♪</i>

681
00:45:24,958 --> 00:45:27,083
<i>♪ I am lost ♪</i>

682
00:45:28,500 --> 00:45:33,500
<i>♪ I don't care at all ♪</i>

683
00:45:39,916 --> 00:45:41,458
WELCOME

684
00:45:49,125 --> 00:45:51,125
AGAIN

685
00:45:51,208 --> 00:45:52,333
(CHUCKLES)

686
00:45:54,291 --> 00:45:56,500
Well, most of you already know the rules,

687
00:45:56,583 --> 00:45:59,333
but since there are some new faces,
I'll remind you.

688
00:45:59,416 --> 00:46:02,250
First of all, there will be
<i>no</i> personal relationships.

689
00:46:04,833 --> 00:46:07,333
- All right, that rule's been…
- (LAUGHS)

690
00:46:08,916 --> 00:46:12,500
The second rule is that we're not allowed
to use first or last names.

691
00:46:12,583 --> 00:46:13,625
NAIROBI: Professor.

692
00:46:14,458 --> 00:46:18,208
Let's cut the bullshit. How will we
be breaking into the Bank of Spain?

693
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:33,208
By making a lot of noise.

694
00:46:34,041 --> 00:46:37,833
MADRID, D-DAY

695
00:46:48,541 --> 00:46:50,500
{\an8}(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

696
00:46:50,583 --> 00:46:52,750
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS)

697
00:47:03,208 --> 00:47:04,208
TOKYO: <i>Nowadays,</i>

698
00:47:04,833 --> 00:47:06,541
<i>wars start with bombings.</i>

699
00:47:07,208 --> 00:47:08,208
<i>So did ours.</i>

700
00:47:14,791 --> 00:47:17,375
(CROWD CLAMORING)

701
00:47:30,416 --> 00:47:34,625
TOKYO: <i>That day, in Madrid,</i>
